Package: cat.llm
Title: LLM-Powered Text Classification for Social Science
Version: 3.1.0
Authors@R: person("Chris", "Soria", email = "chrissoria@berkeley.edu",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Meta-package that installs and loads the full CatLLM ecosystem
    for LLM-powered text classification across domains. Installing cat.llm
    brings in cat.stack (general-purpose engine), cat.survey (survey
    responses), cat.vader (social media), cat.ademic (academic papers),
    cat.cog (cognitive assessment), cat.pol (policy documents), and
    cat.web (web content). Like the tidyverse, you can install the full
    ecosystem or individual domain packages.
License: GPL (>= 3)
URL: https://christophersoria.com/cat-llm/cat.llm/, https://github.com/chrissoria/cat-llm
BugReports: https://github.com/chrissoria/cat-llm/issues
Depends:
    R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports:
    cat.stack (>= 0.1.0),
    cat.survey (>= 0.1.0),
    cat.vader (>= 0.1.0),
    cat.ademic (>= 0.1.0),
    cat.cog (>= 0.1.0),
    cat.pol (>= 0.1.0),
    cat.web (>= 0.1.0),
    reticulate (>= 1.28)
